TITLE: Goldman's checking account for the masses nears as bank tests product with U.S. employees
SUMMARY: Goldman's play to manage Americans' primary transaction hub is one of the significant steps it has taken to compete directly with giants such as Wells Fargo.

TITLE: It’s the French election this weekend — here’s what Wall Street expects to happen
SUMMARY: The outcome is far from certain, according to Wall Street, which is predicting potential market shocks in the case of a Le Pen victory.

SUMMARY: In a tweet on Friday, the Tesla CEO admitted that he asked Gates if he was short-selling shares of the electric carmaker.

TITLE: Netflix is finally going after password sharing. Here's how it's likely to work
SUMMARY: Netflix doesn't plan to shut down password sharers overnight. Rather, it intends to bill shared accounts an extra fee in a global rollout that may take a year.

SUMMARY: The European Union agreed on new digital regulations Friday that will force tech giants like to police illegal content on their platforms more aggressively.

SUMMARY: Nearly a month since Covid restrictions began in earnest in Shanghai, foreign businesses say that less than half of their employees are able to return to work.

TITLE: SpaceX signs first Starlink inflight Wi-Fi deal with charter carrier JSX
